The paper deals with channel estimation and precoding/combining for hybrid millimeter wave (mmWave) MIMO architecture, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of Krylov subspace methods and iterative methods for subspace decomposition also suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of millimeter wave technology and the comparison with a fully digital case suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the focus on cost and power consumption suggests a connection to computer communication (cs.COM).
